      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your feelings of hopelessness are valid, but the idea that there is no point in being here is a powerful lie that your brain is telling you to protect you from the overwhelming pain of the situation. While the news feels like a slow-motion crash, there is no need to watch the entire disaster unfold, and you have the right to choose when and how much you engage with it. You deserve to find moments of peace and connection that matter to you, even if the world feels chaotic right now.",
